main event: A flashing object the size and brightness of a second magnitude star was observed flying from west to east at high speed over the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 1 minute, decreasing in elevation from 30 degrees to 20 degrees above the horizon.
The report includes a Project 10073 record card with limited information about the observation.
The report was distributed to various military and intelligence agencies, including the National Security Agency and Defense Intelligence Agency.
The report indicates that the observed object was a UFO, but there is insufficient data for identification.
The sighting occurred on May 29, 1964 in the Pacific Ocean at coordinates 44N 174W.
sighted object: a flashing object the size and brightness of a second magnitude star
